  "timeframe": "15m",
  "market_context": "After a consolidation phase and a break lower, price reaches into a fair value gap on the ETH 15-minute chart. A candle 2 closure forms at the FVG, raising the question of whether a bearish continuation will follow.",
  "key_observation": "Price reached the fair value gap with a candle 2 closure but failed to produce a continuation lower; instead it reversed back up to run the high. Waiting for continuation confirmation kept the trader out of a losing short at the lows.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the prior consolidation and the breakout lower on the 15-minute ETH chart.",
    "Step 2: Observe price reaching into a fair value gap and forming a candle 2 closure as a potential reversal/continuation signal.",
    "Step 3: Wait for continuation confirmation rather than shorting the lows immediately at the candle 2 closure.",
    "Step 4: Note that continuation does not form — the protected swing remains intact and price reverses up to take out the high.",
    "Step 5: After the high is run, price trades lower again, taking out short-term lows; require further continuation confirmation before engaging.",
    "Step 6: Confirm the bearish continuation when price retests the level and then continues lower."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Waiting for continuation confirmation after a candle 2 closure at a fair value gap protects against shorting the lows when the move is actually a reversal. The protected swing rule keeps you out of bad trades and lets you re-engage when true continuation appears.",
